operations.CreateCrossAccountAuthorization: Creates a cross-account readiness authorization. This lets you authorize another account to work with Route 53 Application Recovery Controller, for example, to check the readiness status of resources in a separate account.
operations.CreateReadinessCheck: Creates a readiness check in an account. A readiness check monitors a resource set in your application, such as a set of Amazon Aurora instances, that Application Recovery Controller is auditing recovery readiness for. The audits run once every minute on every resource that's associated with a readiness check.
operations.CreateRecoveryGroup: Creates a recovery group in an account. A recovery group corresponds to an application and includes a list of the cells that make up the application.
operations.CreateResourceSet: Creates a resource set. A resource set is a set of resources of one type that span multiple cells. You can associate a resource set with a readiness check to monitor the resources for failover readiness.
operations.DeleteCell: Delete a cell. When successful, the response code is 204, with no response body.
operations.GetArchitectureRecommendations: Gets recommendations about architecture designs for improving resiliency for an application, based on a recovery group.
operations.GetCell: Gets information about a cell including cell name, cell Amazon Resource Name (ARN), ARNs of nested cells for this cell, and a list of those cell ARNs with their associated recovery group ARNs.
operations.GetCellReadinessSummary: Gets readiness for a cell. Aggregates the readiness of all the resources that are associated with the cell into a single value.
operations.GetReadinessCheckResourceStatus: Gets individual readiness status for a readiness check. To see the overall readiness status for a recovery group, that considers the readiness status for all the readiness checks in the recovery group, use GetRecoveryGroupReadinessSummary.
operations.GetReadinessCheckStatus: Gets the readiness status for an individual readiness check. To see the overall readiness status for a recovery group, that considers the readiness status for all the readiness checks in a recovery group, use GetRecoveryGroupReadinessSummary.
operations.GetRecoveryGroup: Gets details about a recovery group, including a list of the cells that are included in it.
operations.GetRecoveryGroupReadinessSummary: Displays a summary of information about a recovery group's readiness status. Includes the readiness checks for resources in the recovery group and the readiness status of each one.
operations.GetResourceSet: Displays the details about a resource set, including a list of the resources in the set.
operations.ListCrossAccountAuthorizations: Lists the cross-account readiness authorizations that are in place for an account.
operations.ListReadinessChecks: Lists the readiness checks for an account.
operations.ListRecoveryGroups: Lists the recovery groups in an account.
operations.ListResourceSets: Lists the resource sets in an account.
operations.ListRules: Lists all readiness rules, or lists the readiness rules for a specific resource type.
operations.UpdateCell: Updates a cell to replace the list of nested cells with a new list of nested cells.
